# Monetization, billing, entitlements, quotas, and ads

Do not implement monetization as demo UI. Monetization must be a real backend-enforced subsystem.

## Required architecture

- Implement a central entitlement service.
- Implement a central quota service.
- Implement billing/payment provider interfaces.
- Implement a local/dev billing provider when real provider keys are unavailable.
- Implement ad provider and ad placement abstractions.
- Store plan, entitlement, quota, subscription, usage, ad placement, and billing audit data in PostgreSQL.
- Enforce restricted features on the backend. Frontend checks are UX only.
- All admin monetization mutations require RBAC and audit logs.

## Forbidden shortcuts

- Do not scatter `user.plan === "premium"` checks across the codebase.
- Do not use frontend-only paywalls.
- Do not fake checkout success without updating subscription tables.
- Do not hard-code ads directly inside random UI components.
- Do not show ads during answer reveal, timed quiz questions, focus sessions, or critical learning moments.
- Do not block access to user-created existing content without a clear policy.
- Do not send sensitive learning content, private notes, or personal search queries to ad providers.

## Minimum entities

The implementation should support these concepts even if the MVP uses a local provider:

- plan
- localized plan display text
- entitlement
- plan entitlement
- quota policy
- subscription
- subscription event
- usage counter
- usage event
- invoice/payment record placeholder
- coupon/promotion placeholder
- admin override
- ad placement
- ad decision
- ad impression/click event
- paywall impression/upgrade event

## UX requirements

- Upgrade prompts must be respectful and clear.
- Free users should understand limits before hitting them where possible.
- Paid plans should remove or reduce ads based on plan configuration.
- Ads must be visually distinguishable from learning actions.
- No dark patterns, fake urgency, or misleading upgrade copy.
